    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen opening the ui2 pager, there is a brief period in between the message window and the pager window where neither are displayed. This looks bad, especially when `laststatus=3`.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/522a4d71-eaba-4398-99d9-43de0eab1089\n\nKey frames in order:\n\n1:\n<img width=\"868\" height=\"562\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2a52dc8f-5331-49f4-b4b4-1fbc5742194b\" />\n\n2 (this one should not appear):\n<img width=\"868\" height=\"562\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dc6b1b2e-b7f7-407f-a7e1-8b906653817a\" />\n\n3:\n<img width=\"868\" height=\"562\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ca260b78-bc5e-4d97-a7d4-d11a1a50222a\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean`\n- `:lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable {}`\n- `:hi`\n- `g<`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo in-between state is drawn.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2711+g5f9bc7c272",
